abstract: New Zealand has narrowed list of potential designs for new flag down to five finalists; more than 10,000 designs had been submitted; many New Zealanders remain unenthusiastic about options.
lead_paragraph: Out of more than 10,000 designs submitted, New Zealanders will vote on five, then decide if the winner should be the new flag, or the old one should keep flying.

headline.main: New Zealand Debates Replacing Union Jack Flag, but With What?
headline.print_headline: New Zealand Narrows Field for Flag Vote to Five Contenders
